You can either be your own worst enemy or your number one fan. When people ask about me having Graves' disease and MS they often make it sound like it's a death sentence. Can it be debilitating? Of course! I count my blessings daily that I'm not worse off like some. People told me I was crazy for working out so hard in the past. I ran a full marathon (26.2 miles) while still training for powerlifting. Some didn't think it could be done. It's gonna have to take a lot more than health stuff to hold me down.
